<topic id='attribute_gs1_global_location_number.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: GS1 GLOBAL LOCATION NUMBER - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A unique number which identifies a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_location">LOCATION</xref>
 within an 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
, for the purposes of 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_gs1">GS1</xref>
 Standards.  </p>
  <p>
The 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_gs1_global_location_number">GS1 GLOBAL LOCATION NUMBER</xref>
 is allocated by the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>
 from the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute"
            keyref="attribute_gs1_unique_organisation_prefix_number">GS1 UNIQUE ORGANISATION PREFIX NUMBER</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
Further guidance can be found on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/isce/publication/dcb1077"
            scope="external"
            format="html">DCB1077: AIDC for Patient Identification.</xref>
  </p>

</body>
